WEBVTT

00:03.903 --> 00:06.473
[scoffs]
This whole thing is a joke.

00:06.539 --> 00:08.241
They don't have a case,
and they know it.

00:08.308 --> 00:12.045
These women are prostitutes
and drug addicts, Dominic.

00:12.112 --> 00:14.981
Every word that comes out
of their mouth is a damn lie.

00:15.048 --> 00:17.550
Like I said,
it's a defensible case.

00:17.617 --> 00:19.719
You'll have your day in court.

00:19.786 --> 00:21.554
[banging on door]
- Phil Grady!

00:21.621 --> 00:23.323
I wanna talk to you!

00:23.390 --> 00:24.791
Who's that?

00:24.858 --> 00:28.395
I have no idea.
[banging on door]

00:30.296 --> 00:31.398
Can I help you?

00:31.464 --> 00:32.799
I know what you did,

00:32.866 --> 00:35.034
and I'm not gonna
just sit around anymore.

00:35.101 --> 00:37.203
Where is she?
- Who?

00:37.270 --> 00:39.005
You know what I'm talking about!

00:39.072 --> 00:40.407
Look, I got no idea what...

00:40.473 --> 00:42.475
Ma'am, this is private property,

00:42.542 --> 00:43.619
and you're trespassing.
You need to go...

00:43.643 --> 00:44.820
Tell me what you did with her!

00:44.844 --> 00:45.979
I mean it!

00:46.045 --> 00:47.547
Leave now,
or I'm calling the police.

00:47.614 --> 00:51.117
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:51.184 --> 00:54.187
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:54.254 --> 00:55.722
[scoffs] You see?

00:55.789 --> 00:57.690
They're all a bunch
of crazy drunks.

00:57.757 --> 01:00.260
Only gonna be more of them
at the courthouse.

01:00.326 --> 01:01.728
Is the press gonna be there?

01:01.795 --> 01:02.896
Yes.

01:02.962 --> 01:04.964
You're gonna walk in,

01:05.031 --> 01:06.433
hold your head high,

01:06.499 --> 01:07.934
and turn yourself in
with dignity.

01:08.001 --> 01:10.403
How you behave in
the first hour sets the tone.

01:10.470 --> 01:12.071
I can't believe this.

01:12.138 --> 01:14.407
The only reason that bitch
prosecutor's charging me

01:14.474 --> 01:16.242
is so she can
get her name in the paper.

01:16.309 --> 01:17.777
Why would I de...
[glass shatters]

01:19.946 --> 01:20.946
[sighs]

01:23.116 --> 01:24.484
Oh, whoa, whoa, easy, easy.

01:24.551 --> 01:28.755
I will not be ignored.

01:28.822 --> 01:29.856
Okay.

01:29.923 --> 01:31.324
Okay.
- Don't touch that, no!

01:31.391 --> 01:32.292
[gunshot]
- [yells]

01:32.358 --> 01:36.996
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:37.063 --> 01:38.064
Listen.

01:38.131 --> 01:39.131
- Back up!
- Okay.

01:39.165 --> 01:40.200
- Back up!
- Okay, look...

01:40.266 --> 01:41.277
- Back! Up!
- Okay, all right.

01:41.301 --> 01:42.602
He didn't give me a choice,

01:42.669 --> 01:44.938
so don't make the same mistake.

01:45.004 --> 01:46.004
I won't, I won't.

01:49.809 --> 01:51.010
Are those your car keys?

01:51.077 --> 01:52.479
Yeah, yeah.

01:52.545 --> 01:53.847
Nice and slow.

01:55.949 --> 01:58.017
[both grunt]

01:58.084 --> 02:05.024
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:09.496 --> 02:11.564
It's called Three Kings Day.

02:11.631 --> 02:13.800
Julie left her shoes
outside her door,

02:13.867 --> 02:15.635
and Jesus brought her presents.

02:15.702 --> 02:17.704
That sounds fun,
but I don't think it's Jesus

02:17.770 --> 02:19.506
that brings the presents, honey.

02:19.572 --> 02:22.108
Why don't we celebrate it?

02:22.175 --> 02:24.244
Well, because
that's not our religion.

02:24.310 --> 02:26.446
What religion are we?

02:26.513 --> 02:27.981
We're just us...

02:28.047 --> 02:31.084
Good people
who are kind to others.

02:31.150 --> 02:33.019
Why don't we go to church?

02:33.086 --> 02:35.188
Sweetie, we don't
have time for this now.

02:35.255 --> 02:36.256
Come on.

02:36.322 --> 02:38.291
Mmm, on you go.

02:38.358 --> 02:39.425
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

02:39.492 --> 02:41.594
[laughing] Come here.

02:41.661 --> 02:43.563
I love you. Be a good listener.

02:43.630 --> 02:44.998
- Good morning.
- Hi.

02:49.569 --> 02:50.703
[grunts]

02:50.770 --> 02:52.839
Don't start.
We've discussed this.

02:52.906 --> 02:54.083
We can't just ignore it, Char.

02:54.107 --> 02:55.308
She's obviously curious.

02:55.375 --> 02:56.876
I'm not brainwashing my child.

02:56.943 --> 02:59.279
Our child,
and it's not brainwashing.

02:59.345 --> 03:02.181
Kids her age,
they crave identity, community.

03:02.248 --> 03:05.018
<i>[soft pensive music]</i>

03:05.084 --> 03:07.587
What could it hurt
to at least let her try it out?

03:07.654 --> 03:10.423
A lot,
and where is this coming from?

03:10.490 --> 03:11.591
I can't even remember

03:11.658 --> 03:13.459
the last time
you went to church.

03:15.194 --> 03:18.331
- Before we were married.
- [laughs] Exactly.

03:18.398 --> 03:20.500
And when they found out
your groom was a bride,

03:20.567 --> 03:22.302
you stopped going.

03:22.368 --> 03:25.038
I'm not putting that on Anais.

03:25.104 --> 03:28.141
That was a long time ago.
Things have changed now.

03:28.207 --> 03:29.676
And you know this how?

03:29.742 --> 03:32.779
My mom goes, and she says
they're a lot more open now.

03:32.845 --> 03:35.782
She also says it's an hour
of peace each week,

03:35.848 --> 03:37.617
where she gets to just sit alone

03:37.684 --> 03:39.152
and not worry about anything.

03:40.954 --> 03:43.556
That sounds pretty good to me.

03:43.623 --> 03:45.525
Fine, if you want some peace

03:45.592 --> 03:47.694
on a Sunday morning,
be my guest.

03:47.760 --> 03:49.662
I'll take the kids to the park.
[phone rings]

03:49.729 --> 03:51.097
One second.

03:51.164 --> 03:52.665
Hey.

03:54.200 --> 03:55.535
Okay.

03:55.602 --> 03:57.203
[clears throat]

03:57.270 --> 03:58.671
Sorry, traffic was a bitch.

03:58.738 --> 04:01.741
This thing queued up?
- Yeah.

04:01.808 --> 04:03.610
Murder-abduction
in Wilmington...

04:03.676 --> 04:05.945
DOA on the floor
is Dominic Howard,

04:06.012 --> 04:07.756
one of the top defense
attorneys in Delaware.

04:07.780 --> 04:09.549
The guy on his right
is his client,

04:09.616 --> 04:11.351
state police detective
Phil Grady.

04:11.417 --> 04:13.720
They were both at Grady's house
when an unknown female

04:13.786 --> 04:16.623
rolled up, shot Howard dead,
and took off with Grady.

04:16.689 --> 04:18.124
Any description?

04:18.190 --> 04:19.902
Neighbor saw what she
described as a homeless woman

04:19.926 --> 04:22.095
exit a cab near Grady's house...
A few minutes later,

04:22.161 --> 04:23.730
heard a gunshot,
then saw the woman

04:23.796 --> 04:25.531
leaving in Grady's car.

04:25.598 --> 04:27.367
BOLO's out on his sedan.

04:27.433 --> 04:28.768
Yesterday, Grady was charged

04:28.835 --> 04:30.903
with assaulting two homeless
women while on duty.

04:30.970 --> 04:33.773
He was set to turn himself in
to the AUSA this morning,

04:33.840 --> 04:35.351
which was why
he was meeting with his lawyer.

04:35.375 --> 04:37.152
And they wonder why
the public doesn't trust us.

04:37.176 --> 04:39.278
State police think
our fugitive could be

04:39.345 --> 04:41.581
one of the homeless women
he allegedly assaulted,

04:41.648 --> 04:42.982
gone vigilante.

04:43.049 --> 04:44.849
And Howard was what,
just collateral damage?

04:44.884 --> 04:46.386
Possibly.
Clock's ticking.

04:46.452 --> 04:47.663
Hana, you take the crime scene.

04:47.687 --> 04:48.764
Barnes and Ray,
you're on the cab driver.

04:48.788 --> 04:49.989
Gaines and I will talk

04:50.056 --> 04:51.357
to the state police
and the AUSA.

04:51.424 --> 04:52.525
Let's roll.

04:52.592 --> 04:55.762
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

04:55.828 --> 04:57.664
I picked her up
at the train station...

04:57.730 --> 04:59.265
Pretty standard ride.

04:59.332 --> 05:01.401
She didn't announce
she was about to kill no guy,

05:01.467 --> 05:02.611
if that's what you're asking.

05:02.635 --> 05:04.115
All right,
did she say anything odd,

05:04.170 --> 05:05.371
give you a name?

05:05.438 --> 05:07.907
Just the address,
and she paid cash...

05:07.974 --> 05:09.652
Told me to keep the tip.
- Well, what about her face?

05:09.676 --> 05:11.577
Can you give us a description?

05:11.644 --> 05:13.112
She had a mask on
the whole time.

05:13.179 --> 05:14.781
Brown hair is all I saw.

05:14.847 --> 05:16.058
But she got off the train,
right?

05:16.082 --> 05:17.917
Don't know
if she was on the train.

05:17.984 --> 05:19.762
I picked her up
on the same side of the station

05:19.786 --> 05:21.087
as the homeless camp.

05:21.154 --> 05:22.914
She looked like
she could've come from there.

05:22.955 --> 05:24.166
She was swigging
from a half-pint

05:24.190 --> 05:25.625
in the back seat the whole time.

05:25.692 --> 05:26.993
Liquid courage.

05:27.060 --> 05:27.860
Maybe.

05:27.927 --> 05:29.796
Sorry, that's all I know.

05:29.862 --> 05:31.497
Thank you for your help.

05:31.564 --> 05:32.965
Why don't you check with Amtrak,

05:33.032 --> 05:35.468
see if we can find anyone
similar on the security cams.

05:35.535 --> 05:37.670
I'll call Remy, let him know
about the homeless camp

05:37.737 --> 05:40.039
by the train station.
- All right.

05:40.106 --> 05:41.674
For years, Grady took advantage

05:41.741 --> 05:43.509
of women in shelters
and encampments.

05:43.576 --> 05:45.178
Two came forward,
but the county DA

05:45.244 --> 05:46.713
refused to press charges.

05:46.779 --> 05:48.347
There was community outcry.

05:48.414 --> 05:50.683
I tried to fire him,
but the union got involved.

05:50.750 --> 05:52.885
I couldn't
unless he was charged,

05:52.952 --> 05:56.055
so we asked DOJ to open
a civil rights investigation.

05:56.122 --> 05:57.857
The charges weren't a slam dunk.

05:57.924 --> 05:59.225
Both victims had a history

05:59.292 --> 06:01.461
of mental health
and substance abuse issues.

06:01.527 --> 06:03.963
One had a conviction
for aggravated assault.

06:04.030 --> 06:05.798
Which could be why
Grady targeted them,

06:05.865 --> 06:07.700
thinking no one
would believe them.

06:07.767 --> 06:08.968
Where are the women now?

06:09.035 --> 06:10.412
One of them is staying
in a halfway house.

06:10.436 --> 06:12.672
I confirmed
she was there this morning.

06:12.739 --> 06:14.006
But this one, Betty,

06:14.073 --> 06:16.075
we haven't been able
to find her.

06:16.142 --> 06:18.077
She's the one convicted
of assault?

06:18.144 --> 06:20.880
Yup, splits her time
between the homeless camps

06:20.947 --> 06:23.716
by the main library
and the train station.

06:23.783 --> 06:25.251
Train station?

06:25.318 --> 06:27.229
Barnes says that's where
the cab driver picked her up.

06:27.253 --> 06:28.554
- Yeah.
- Have a look into that.

06:28.621 --> 06:30.556
Will do.

06:30.623 --> 06:32.825
Thank you very much.

06:32.892 --> 06:34.961
Excuse me,
I'm an agent with the FBI.

06:35.027 --> 06:36.867
I'm just wondering
if you happened to have seen

06:36.896 --> 06:38.798
this woman around?
She answers to Betty.

06:38.865 --> 06:40.299
- No.
- No? Okay.

06:40.366 --> 06:42.277
Get away from me.
All you cops, get out of here.

06:42.301 --> 06:43.581
Look, I'm not tryna bother you,

06:43.636 --> 06:44.646
all right, I just need to know

06:44.670 --> 06:46.372
if you have seen this woman.

06:46.439 --> 06:47.540
Her name is Betty.

06:47.607 --> 06:48.851
She don't
come around here no more

06:48.875 --> 06:50.115
after what you pigs did to her.

06:50.143 --> 06:52.111
Then you know where she went?

06:52.178 --> 06:54.213
I don't have to
tell you nothin'.

06:54.280 --> 06:55.615
I know my rights.

06:55.681 --> 06:57.049
Get out of here.

06:57.116 --> 06:59.185
Go on!

06:59.252 --> 07:00.753
- You got anything?
- Nope.

07:00.820 --> 07:02.688
[sighs]
- They're not gonna help us.

07:02.755 --> 07:04.490
They all think
we're as bad as Grady.

07:04.557 --> 07:08.494
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:08.561 --> 07:11.497
- What do you think?
- I think that's her.

07:11.564 --> 07:13.399
Hey! Betty!

07:14.867 --> 07:16.102
Hey!
- Where she goin'?

07:16.169 --> 07:17.870
Hey,
I just wanted to talk to you!

07:17.937 --> 07:22.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:22.074 --> 07:24.477
Hey, there she is!

07:24.544 --> 07:25.711
Hey!

07:30.583 --> 07:31.818
She went around back!

07:31.884 --> 07:33.019
Okay, she's coming back!

07:35.922 --> 07:37.089
I got her.

07:37.156 --> 07:38.156
Hey!

07:42.128 --> 07:43.129
Okay.

07:43.196 --> 07:44.764
Okay!
Just get it over with.

07:44.831 --> 07:45.898
Get what over with?

07:45.965 --> 07:47.205
I know I'm on my third strike.

07:47.266 --> 07:48.601
Take me back to county already.

07:48.668 --> 07:50.603
We are FBI, not Narcotics.

07:50.670 --> 07:52.505
We're looking for Phil Grady.

07:52.572 --> 07:54.006
Shady Grady?

07:54.073 --> 07:55.341
I hate that son of a bitch.

07:55.408 --> 07:56.585
Is that why you went
to his house this morning

07:56.609 --> 07:59.278
and kidnapped him
after killing his lawyer?

07:59.345 --> 08:00.713
What? No!

08:00.780 --> 08:04.217
Wait... I went to the Dunkin'
on Avalon this morning

08:04.283 --> 08:06.018
to dive for yesterday's donuts.
I swear.

08:06.085 --> 08:07.620
You can check.
- Good idea.

08:07.687 --> 08:09.188
Smile.
- What for?

08:09.255 --> 08:10.895
You better hope
you're on those cameras.

08:10.957 --> 08:12.892
I got her.

08:12.959 --> 08:15.127
What if Grady
had another victim, right?

08:15.194 --> 08:17.363
Somebody we don't know about?

08:17.430 --> 08:19.031
Then we're fresh out of leads.

08:21.834 --> 08:23.469
- Hurry up.
- Where are we?

08:23.536 --> 08:24.737
You're about to see.

08:24.804 --> 08:26.505
Please,
just tell me what you want.

08:26.572 --> 08:28.441
What I want is the truth.

08:28.507 --> 08:30.586
If you give that to me,
we're not gonna have a problem.

08:30.610 --> 08:33.679
Sit.
- [grunts]

08:33.746 --> 08:40.852
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:41.520 --> 08:42.955
Oh, my God.

08:43.022 --> 08:46.525
Wh... why are we here?

08:46.592 --> 08:48.394
Because I wanna know
how you did it.

08:48.461 --> 08:49.996
Did what?
I have no idea what...

08:50.062 --> 08:53.399
Don't turn around.

08:53.466 --> 08:56.969
See that over there?
That's where it all started.

08:57.036 --> 09:00.139
They're tearing it down now
to destroy the evidence.

09:00.206 --> 09:01.874
They're not destroying evidence.

09:01.941 --> 09:03.509
They're razing the camp.

09:03.576 --> 09:04.586
People were slaughtered here.

09:04.610 --> 09:05.912
Kids were slaughtered here...

09:05.978 --> 09:08.648
That's what you want us
to think, right?

09:08.714 --> 09:09.925
When you brought in the cadavers

09:09.949 --> 09:11.484
to replace the crisis actors?

09:11.550 --> 09:12.652
What?

09:12.718 --> 09:14.196
I-I didn't investigate
this case, lady.

09:14.220 --> 09:16.622
Don't call me that.

09:16.689 --> 09:18.190
You know who I am.

09:18.257 --> 09:20.226
I have no idea who you are.

09:22.295 --> 09:24.430
- Well, you know my husband.
- What?

09:24.497 --> 09:26.132
Don't you?

09:26.198 --> 09:28.768
You're the one who gave him
that fake picture

09:28.834 --> 09:32.538
of my baby girl supposedly
shot in the face so many times

09:32.605 --> 09:35.374
she was unrecognizable.

09:35.441 --> 09:36.943
[sighs]

09:37.009 --> 09:39.779
Wasn't that convenient?

09:39.845 --> 09:41.847
You're Mya Fogelman's mom.

09:43.182 --> 09:45.084
Mass shooting
at a Delaware summer camp.

09:45.151 --> 09:48.087
We are very sorry
about what happened to Mya.

09:48.154 --> 09:50.022
<i>We don't need
thoughts and prayers.</i>

09:50.089 --> 09:51.667
I can barely get out
of bed in the morning.

09:51.691 --> 09:55.361
<i>We want someone
to stop this madness!</i>

09:55.428 --> 09:58.965
I wanna show you a photograph
of my daughter, Mya.

10:00.132 --> 10:02.101
Where is she?

10:02.168 --> 10:04.737
Wha... what do you mean?

10:04.804 --> 10:06.772
She... she's... she's dead.
- Liar!

10:06.839 --> 10:10.343
This whole thing was a fake
and false flag operation,

10:10.409 --> 10:13.245
which means
somebody took my Mya.

10:13.312 --> 10:14.880
Who was it?
- I... I... I don't know.

10:14.947 --> 10:17.016
Tell me where she is!

10:17.083 --> 10:19.085
I can't tell you
what I don't know.

10:20.987 --> 10:22.621
Listen, I... I...
I know you're upset,

10:22.688 --> 10:24.690
an... and you wanna believe
Mya's still alive.

10:24.757 --> 10:27.126
She <i> is!</i>

10:27.193 --> 10:28.861
And I'm going to find her.

10:28.928 --> 10:30.363
I... I understand,

10:30.429 --> 10:33.232
but you're not thinking
clearly right now.

10:33.299 --> 10:34.500
Let me...

10:34.567 --> 10:36.335
Let me help you.

10:36.402 --> 10:39.071
I know people you can talk to.

10:40.873 --> 10:42.241
This whole thing will be okay.

10:43.509 --> 10:47.413
All right?
Just let me help you.

10:47.480 --> 10:48.480
I promise.

10:54.086 --> 10:56.322
I promise.
Please.

10:58.657 --> 11:00.793
You had your chance.

11:00.860 --> 11:01.860
No!

11:01.894 --> 11:02.828
No... [gunshot]

11:02.895 --> 11:06.632
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:12.505 --> 11:15.508
[indistinct chatter]

11:17.243 --> 11:19.779
This is the site
of the summer camp massacre.

11:19.845 --> 11:21.914
Four months ago,
a loser named Vincent Fleming

11:21.981 --> 11:24.016
shot his father
and his therapist at his house

11:24.083 --> 11:28.254
then drove here and killed
seven kids and a counselor,

11:28.320 --> 11:30.689
surrendered after a shootout
and died the next day.

11:30.756 --> 11:32.024
Whole place feels haunted.

11:32.091 --> 11:33.692
No wonder
they're tearing it down.

11:33.759 --> 11:35.694
[sighs] We've been
monitoring his cell...

11:35.761 --> 11:37.096
Finally pinged an hour ago.

11:37.163 --> 11:39.799
Same for us,
but when we got here,

11:39.865 --> 11:43.035
your unsub was gone,
and so was Grady's cell.

11:43.102 --> 11:44.670
Whoever did this
must have taken it,

11:44.737 --> 11:46.272
but it's off now.

11:46.338 --> 11:48.874
Was Grady involved in the
response to the camp shooting?

11:48.941 --> 11:50.609
No, we had a special task force,

11:50.676 --> 11:52.011
but he wasn't on it.

11:52.078 --> 11:54.046
Well, then why target him
and bring him here?

11:54.113 --> 11:55.815
<i>[solemn music]</i>

11:55.881 --> 11:57.883
Guys, I got something.

12:00.419 --> 12:02.421
they claim is of Grady.

12:02.488 --> 12:04.824
<i>This is a warning
to everyone involved</i>

12:04.890 --> 12:08.227
<i>in this conspiracy,
all you liars.</i>

12:10.162 --> 12:12.565
<i>I don't care what I have to do.</i>

12:12.631 --> 12:14.600
<i>I'm gonna find the truth,</i>

12:14.667 --> 12:16.135
<i>and I'm gonna find my daughter.</i>

12:16.202 --> 12:18.437
Now, you remember
who that is, right?

12:18.504 --> 12:20.339
Kim Fogelman.

12:20.406 --> 12:21.407
You know her?

12:21.474 --> 12:22.474
Her daughter, Mya.

12:22.508 --> 12:24.210
She was killed here.

12:24.276 --> 12:25.787
We interviewed her
because her husband

12:25.811 --> 12:27.613
got so angry, he bought an AR-15

12:27.680 --> 12:29.215
and kidnapped
the head of the NRF

12:29.281 --> 12:31.117
and forced him
to post a picture of dead Mya

12:31.183 --> 12:32.551
at gunpoint
before he surrendered.

12:32.618 --> 12:34.253
We're the ones
who put him in prison.

12:34.320 --> 12:36.122
So we can forget about
our homeless woman

12:36.188 --> 12:37.690
vigilante theory.

12:37.756 --> 12:39.201
Mya's dead, but she's still
looking for her.

12:39.225 --> 12:41.260
She obviously thinks
that Mya is still alive.

12:41.327 --> 12:42.928
The question is why.

12:42.995 --> 12:45.397
Tanya Waters, she's
a conspiracy theory queen.

12:45.464 --> 12:47.833
She claims that this
entire camp shooting was fake.

12:47.900 --> 12:49.201
Great, can't wait to meet her.

12:49.268 --> 12:51.337
You two grab Kristin
and cover Kim's house.

12:51.403 --> 12:52.505
She has a sister, right?

12:52.571 --> 12:54.173
Liliana... lives in Elsmere.

12:54.240 --> 12:55.684
All right,
let's get ahold of her too.

12:55.708 --> 12:57.452
We need to know what happened
these last four months

12:57.476 --> 13:00.312
to make a grieving mother snap.

13:00.379 --> 13:03.282
I don't condone violence,
and I don't condone murder,

13:03.349 --> 13:05.084
but I will say this...

13:05.151 --> 13:08.821
If you were a mother,
and you knew your child

13:08.888 --> 13:13.058
was alive, what would
you be willing to do?

13:13.125 --> 13:15.561
Don't mess with the mama bear,
people.

13:15.628 --> 13:17.696
She bites.

13:20.466 --> 13:21.600
And we're out.
[bell rings]

13:21.667 --> 13:23.502
Whoo.

13:23.569 --> 13:25.504
Thank you, people.

13:25.571 --> 13:27.173
Agent Scott, FBI.

13:27.239 --> 13:29.408
Congratulations
on the world's worst acting.

13:29.475 --> 13:31.644
Oh, nice to meet you too.

13:31.710 --> 13:34.013
You need to stop
running that video.

13:34.079 --> 13:35.648
Of course we're running it.

13:35.714 --> 13:37.716
We're gonna run everything
she sends us.

13:37.783 --> 13:39.685
Kim Fogelman
is exposing the truth.

13:39.752 --> 13:40.786
How do you know Kim?

13:40.853 --> 13:42.288
I don't.
Five minutes, Grace.

13:42.354 --> 13:43.832
Then why did
she send you that video?

13:43.856 --> 13:45.024
She didn't.

13:45.090 --> 13:48.994
Some guy named Phil Grady
emailed it to us.

13:49.061 --> 13:50.563
So she stole the phone
to record it

13:50.629 --> 13:51.730
and then get rid of it.

13:51.797 --> 13:55.167
I am glad... thank you...
That she sent it.

13:55.234 --> 13:57.536
We encourage
our citizen journalists

13:57.603 --> 13:58.843
to share their stories with us.

13:58.871 --> 14:00.339
She's a murderer,

14:00.406 --> 14:01.740
not a journalist,

14:01.807 --> 14:02.984
and she may have been influenced

14:03.008 --> 14:04.777
by one of your
wack conspiracy theories.

14:04.843 --> 14:06.579
Theories?

14:06.645 --> 14:08.380
I ask questions...

14:08.447 --> 14:10.182
Questions any thinking person

14:10.249 --> 14:12.384
would be asking
of their government.

14:12.451 --> 14:16.021
I am not in control of
or responsible for what happens

14:16.088 --> 14:17.990
when one of my viewers
find their answers.

14:18.057 --> 14:21.060
Right, so we will need to see
the documents and the tapes,

14:21.126 --> 14:22.370
see what kind of questions
you're asking

14:22.394 --> 14:23.395
about the camp shooting.

14:23.462 --> 14:24.830
Do you have a warrant?

14:24.897 --> 14:27.266
Look, this woman
murdered two people,

14:27.333 --> 14:29.435
and we need to know what
she could be planning next.

14:29.501 --> 14:32.404
So my first amendment rights
go out the window?

14:33.872 --> 14:36.475
Pulling that video
shows prior constraint.

14:36.542 --> 14:38.644
Revealing confidential sources

14:38.711 --> 14:40.012
violates a reporter's privilege.

14:40.079 --> 14:42.081
Do you think I haven't
been threatened before?

14:43.716 --> 14:45.317
"Whoever would
overthrow a nation

14:45.384 --> 14:49.521
must begin by subduing
the freeness of speech,"

14:49.588 --> 14:50.789
Benjamin Franklin.

14:50.856 --> 14:53.592
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

14:53.659 --> 14:55.594
"I'll be back,"

14:55.661 --> 14:56.962
Arnold Schwarzenegger.

15:00.666 --> 15:03.435
Deep dive every river of BS
she put on the camp shooting.

15:03.502 --> 15:05.604
Let's make this bitch's life
a living hell.

15:05.671 --> 15:07.206
My pleasure.

15:07.273 --> 15:10.376
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:10.442 --> 15:12.177
- Liliana?
- Yes.

15:12.244 --> 15:14.113
I'm Sheryll.
We spoke on the phone.

15:14.179 --> 15:15.590
You have the keys
to your sister's house?

15:15.614 --> 15:16.849
Yeah, I was waiting for you.

15:16.915 --> 15:18.317
I'll have to clear it first.

15:22.321 --> 15:23.422
Kim's not here.

15:23.489 --> 15:25.591
House is empty.

15:25.658 --> 15:26.935
We saw a neighbor
across the street.

15:26.959 --> 15:28.727
I'm gonna go see
what she has to say.

15:30.829 --> 15:32.631
Oh, my God.

15:32.698 --> 15:34.667
What a mess.

15:34.733 --> 15:37.236
I had no idea
she was living like this.

15:37.303 --> 15:39.238
When was the last time
you were here?

15:39.305 --> 15:40.606
A month ago.

15:40.673 --> 15:42.107
Kim stopped returning my calls.

15:42.174 --> 15:43.976
I thought she was just busy.

15:44.043 --> 15:46.078
Your sister likes her wine.

15:46.145 --> 15:47.465
She's not supposed to have that.

15:47.513 --> 15:49.548
She was an alcoholic.
Josh made her go to AA.

15:49.615 --> 15:51.216
She's been sober 12 years.

15:51.283 --> 15:53.886
Grief can do that sometimes.

15:56.188 --> 15:58.524
She bought Mya Christmas gifts.

15:58.590 --> 16:00.959
Who knows how long
she's been in denial.

16:01.026 --> 16:03.295
The holidays might have been
what triggered it.

16:05.230 --> 16:07.099
Hey, Liliana,
where was Mya's room?

16:07.166 --> 16:08.734
Down the hall on the right.

16:08.801 --> 16:10.836
Okay, thank you.

16:17.076 --> 16:19.645
<i>[solemn music]</i>

16:19.712 --> 16:21.280
It's a shrine to her daughter.

16:22.881 --> 16:26.685
She has a dentist appointment
scheduled for Mya next week.

16:26.752 --> 16:29.054
Looks like she's lived
every day since the shooting

16:29.121 --> 16:31.156
believing Mya's alive
and coming home.

16:31.223 --> 16:32.591
[vacuum whirring]
- Hey, Liliana,

16:32.658 --> 16:34.259
you don't have to do that.

16:34.326 --> 16:35.627
Please.

16:35.694 --> 16:37.494
[vacuum whirs down]
Why don't you take a seat?

16:39.231 --> 16:40.332
Come on.

16:43.035 --> 16:44.403
What can you tell us about Kim?

16:44.470 --> 16:46.472
What was she like
after the shooting happened?

16:46.538 --> 16:49.241
Kim couldn't
accept Mya was gone.

16:50.776 --> 16:52.053
She didn't even
go to the funeral

16:52.077 --> 16:53.779
of her own daughter.

16:53.846 --> 16:55.023
I had to make the arrangements.

16:55.047 --> 16:56.749
I had to pick up.

16:56.815 --> 16:58.784
Mya's personal effects
from the police.

16:58.851 --> 17:00.452
I still have them
in a box at home.

17:00.519 --> 17:02.654
Did she ever mention
someone called Tanya Waters?

17:02.721 --> 17:05.022
No, not to me.

17:05.089 --> 17:06.224
She didn't talk to anyone,

17:06.290 --> 17:07.992
especially
after Josh got arrested.

17:08.060 --> 17:09.994
She was just alone...

17:10.061 --> 17:12.330
[sobbing]
Alone, sad, and grieving.

17:12.397 --> 17:13.598
I feel awful.

17:13.665 --> 17:15.467
- I'm sorry.
- I spoke with the neighbor.

17:15.534 --> 17:18.337
She said a guy's been visiting
Kim over the last month or so.

17:18.404 --> 17:19.914
No name,
but he drives a pickup truck...

17:19.938 --> 17:21.006
Pennsylvania plates.

17:21.073 --> 17:22.374
Do you know who that could be?

17:22.441 --> 17:25.109
- No.
- I'll inform Remy.

17:25.176 --> 17:27.146
He's on his way
to see Josh Fogelman now.

17:28.881 --> 17:30.249
I thought Kim's denial

17:30.315 --> 17:32.751
was a normal part
of grief at first,

17:32.818 --> 17:35.687
but it went to a whole
new level around Halloween.

17:35.754 --> 17:36.889
What happened?

17:36.955 --> 17:38.357
She started watching
Tanya Waters,

17:38.424 --> 17:41.126
bought into this
whole false flag thing...

17:41.193 --> 17:43.262
How the government
supposedly hired actors

17:43.328 --> 17:46.031
to stage the shooting.
- [sighs]

17:46.098 --> 17:48.467
She even thought
Grady was involved.

17:48.534 --> 17:50.102
Why Grady?

17:50.169 --> 17:52.137
She didn't believe a cop
who wasn't on the case

17:52.204 --> 17:53.906
would get me
a photo of Mya's body

17:53.972 --> 17:57.309
unless he was part
of the conspiracy.

17:58.744 --> 18:01.146
She said it was a cadaver.

18:01.213 --> 18:03.816
But Mya's body
was identified with DNA.

18:03.882 --> 18:05.117
Kim didn't care.

18:05.184 --> 18:06.552
She said that,
according to Tanya,

18:06.618 --> 18:10.622
the government
can fake DNA evidence.

18:10.689 --> 18:13.358
Last time I saw her,
around Thanksgiving,

18:13.425 --> 18:18.030
she was in here screaming
that I was a liar and a pawn,

18:18.096 --> 18:19.898
and they'd kidnapped Mya,

18:19.965 --> 18:21.967
and I wasn't
doing anything about it.

18:22.034 --> 18:24.837
Has she always been
conspiracy-minded?

18:24.903 --> 18:26.138
A little.

18:26.205 --> 18:28.907
- Hmm.
- Her mom was a Cuban exile.

18:28.974 --> 18:30.476
Her family saw firsthand

18:30.542 --> 18:33.479
how governments fabricate
narratives for their own gain,

18:33.545 --> 18:35.914
things like denying
the moon landing happened...

18:35.981 --> 18:38.784
Nothing near this level of BS.

18:38.851 --> 18:41.220
I don't know
how she fell for it.

18:41.286 --> 18:45.757
Tanya presented an easier
reality for her to accept.

18:45.824 --> 18:47.392
This is my fault.

18:47.459 --> 18:50.229
If I'd been there, I would've
taken her back to AA,

18:50.295 --> 18:54.066
and she never would've
found Tanya Waters.

18:54.132 --> 18:56.735
Are you aware
she may have a boyfriend?

18:56.802 --> 18:59.705
Someone from Pennsylvania.

18:59.771 --> 19:01.740
A boyfriend?

19:01.807 --> 19:03.141
No.

19:03.208 --> 19:04.776
I have no idea
who that could be.

19:04.843 --> 19:05.978
I didn't, um...

19:08.080 --> 19:09.481
Know.

19:09.548 --> 19:11.583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:11.650 --> 19:14.286
<i>They want us to believe
that this here...</i>

19:14.353 --> 19:16.488
That's a lot of ranting
with few actual facts.

19:16.555 --> 19:19.157
She's anti-vaxxer,
the election was stolen,

19:19.224 --> 19:21.260
blah, blah, blah,
but her bread and butter

19:21.326 --> 19:22.937
is the mass shootings
like the one at the camp.

19:22.961 --> 19:25.864
She claims they were staged by
the government to scare people

19:25.931 --> 19:28.212
into letting us take their
civil liberties away from them.

19:28.267 --> 19:29.377
How did the government
supposedly

19:29.401 --> 19:30.636
pull this off in our case?

19:30.702 --> 19:31.870
It activated the shooter,

19:31.937 --> 19:34.106
the Delaware State Police,
the coroner,

19:34.172 --> 19:36.141
the company that cleaned up
the crime scene,

19:36.208 --> 19:37.876
even the media
had a part to play.

19:37.943 --> 19:39.463
And does Tanya
think Mya's alive too?

19:39.511 --> 19:41.446
Oh, I doubt she believes
any of this crap,

19:41.513 --> 19:44.182
but her followers
do her work for her.

19:44.249 --> 19:47.920
These are the TanyaDossier
message boards.

19:47.986 --> 19:49.721
According to
whoever posted this,

19:49.788 --> 19:52.691
that is Mya after
a school bombing in Syria,

19:52.758 --> 19:55.694
and now Tanya is claiming
that Mya and the other kids

19:55.761 --> 19:56.895
were taken from the camp,

19:56.962 --> 19:58.402
that they fly them
all over the world

19:58.430 --> 19:59.965
and use them as crisis actors

20:00.032 --> 20:01.833
and other false flag attacks.

20:01.900 --> 20:03.111
Did she say who
in the government

20:03.135 --> 20:04.503
is supposedly doing this?

20:04.570 --> 20:06.481
Well, originally,
it was some mysterious cabal,

20:06.505 --> 20:08.640
but now Tanya's teasing
that she's found the person

20:08.707 --> 20:10.809
that's behind it all...
Someone that they call Mr. X.

20:10.876 --> 20:14.146
I'm sure Mr. X is made-up,
but we're gonna ask her anyway.

20:14.212 --> 20:15.414
Hana Banana, you're with me.

20:15.480 --> 20:16.858
The rest of you,
contact the other families.

20:16.882 --> 20:18.016
Get protection on them.

20:18.083 --> 20:19.818
See if any of this stuff
is real.

20:19.885 --> 20:22.788
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:22.854 --> 20:29.962
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:30.596 --> 20:34.132
Tell me who activated your son.

20:34.199 --> 20:36.768
I know you were a part of this.

20:36.835 --> 20:39.037
[sobbing] I... I told you.

20:39.104 --> 20:41.106
I don't know
what you're talking about.

20:41.173 --> 20:43.208
Yes, you do.

20:43.275 --> 20:45.410
The woman who came here
to see Vincent

20:45.477 --> 20:46.778
on the day that it happened.

20:46.845 --> 20:49.615
Do you mean Dr. Mendoza,
his therapist?

20:49.681 --> 20:51.450
She's not a doctor.

20:51.516 --> 20:53.385
She's a government operative.

20:54.786 --> 20:58.223
She came here,
gave Vincent the gun

20:58.290 --> 20:59.992
and his instructions,

21:00.058 --> 21:02.861
and then he shot her
and your husband

21:02.928 --> 21:04.196
before he went to the camp.

21:04.262 --> 21:05.764
That's not what happened.

21:08.867 --> 21:10.569
Vincent was deeply troubled,

21:10.636 --> 21:12.671
and he wouldn't leave the house.

21:12.738 --> 21:15.107
I'd gone to work, and my
husband called the doctor over,

21:15.173 --> 21:16.775
because he was
so concerned about him.

21:16.842 --> 21:19.177
We didn't even know
Vincent had the gun.

21:20.812 --> 21:23.148
Please.

21:23.215 --> 21:25.851
I know what it feels like

21:25.917 --> 21:27.352
to lose a child.

21:27.419 --> 21:30.055
Vincent did a terrible,
awful thing,

21:30.122 --> 21:32.791
and I am so ashamed
and so, so sorry,

21:32.858 --> 21:34.993
but I promise
I don't know anything

21:35.060 --> 21:36.762
about what you're saying.

21:36.828 --> 21:43.769
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:50.075 --> 21:54.146
I didn't lose a child.

21:54.212 --> 21:58.216
My Mya is still alive,

21:58.283 --> 22:00.719
and I'm going to find
the people that took her.

22:00.786 --> 22:03.055
[sobs]

22:03.121 --> 22:04.790
Who paid you?

22:04.856 --> 22:06.158
What?

22:06.224 --> 22:08.126
You could've gone out
and bought a big house

22:08.193 --> 22:11.363
and nice things,
but you're still here.

22:11.430 --> 22:14.332
I'm still here, because
nobody will buy this house.

22:14.399 --> 22:16.301
Everybody knows who lived here.

22:16.368 --> 22:20.939
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:21.006 --> 22:22.307
Get up.
Come on.

22:22.374 --> 22:23.742
- [crying]
- Over here.

22:23.809 --> 22:25.143
Hurry up.

22:27.746 --> 22:28.746
Sit.

22:30.882 --> 22:34.553
[crying] Please.
I don't know anything.

22:34.619 --> 22:36.221
All right.
What's the password?

22:36.288 --> 22:37.856
There's nothing on there.

22:37.923 --> 22:40.625
Tell me the password!

22:47.766 --> 22:48.766
[sighs]

22:48.800 --> 22:50.502
[groans]

22:50.569 --> 22:52.304
You claim to know
who's behind all this.

22:52.370 --> 22:54.840
So tell us.
Who's this mysterious Mr. X?

22:54.906 --> 22:56.875
Well, first,
thanks for watching,

22:56.942 --> 22:58.977
and second,
that is confidential.

22:59.044 --> 23:01.580
Do you have a name?

23:01.646 --> 23:03.482
It is my patriotic duty

23:03.548 --> 23:06.184
to stand up to you FBI bullies.

23:06.251 --> 23:08.487
Do you have any coherent
theory about this at all,

23:08.553 --> 23:11.790
or do you just do this to sell
your dietary supplements?

23:11.857 --> 23:14.226
See? You are bullies.

23:14.292 --> 23:15.536
[whispering]
I just phoned her.

23:15.560 --> 23:17.395
She's standing by,
ready to speak to you.

23:17.462 --> 23:19.598
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

23:19.664 --> 23:22.734
Okay, let's start the show now.

23:22.801 --> 23:24.269
We'll take it live.

23:24.336 --> 23:25.336
Live?

23:25.370 --> 23:27.873
Are you sure?
- Oh, yeah.

23:27.939 --> 23:29.908
Let's go.
- What the hell's going on?

23:29.975 --> 23:30.842
All right, come on, people.
Move it.

23:30.909 --> 23:32.077
We're live right now.

23:32.144 --> 23:34.813
Now!
- Let's go, people.

23:34.880 --> 23:37.415
Can you handle this for me?
Thank you.

23:37.482 --> 23:41.486
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:41.553 --> 23:42.754
Welcome, my friends.

23:42.821 --> 23:45.090
We are coming
to you early today,

23:45.157 --> 23:48.226
because we have an exclusive
one-on-one interview

23:48.293 --> 23:50.028
with the woman who is fighting

23:50.095 --> 23:52.831
to expose the truth,
Kim Fogelman.

23:52.898 --> 23:56.635
Kim, welcome to TanyaDossier.

23:56.701 --> 23:59.070
<i>Tanya, I found it.</i>

23:59.137 --> 24:00.548
- Shouldn't we cut this off?
- Not yet.

24:00.572 --> 24:02.040
Trace the call.
<i>- I have the proof.</i>

24:02.107 --> 24:04.543
- I'm on it.
<i>- It was on the laptop...</i>

24:04.609 --> 24:08.079
<i>On her laptop.</i>

24:08.146 --> 24:11.283
<i>I know who's behind all of this.</i>

24:11.349 --> 24:12.918
<i>I know...</i>
- Holy crap,

24:12.984 --> 24:14.486
that's Penny Fleming.
- Who?

24:14.553 --> 24:16.430
Her son, Vincent,
was the shooter at the camp.

24:16.454 --> 24:18.223
We can't have
a public execution.

24:18.290 --> 24:19.524
Cut the feed.
- I can't...

24:19.591 --> 24:20.768
- Just kill the feed.
- No, no, I'm not...

24:20.792 --> 24:22.127
Kill the feed.

24:22.194 --> 24:24.830
Kim, this is
Special Agent Remy Scott.

24:24.896 --> 24:26.274
We met a few months ago
at your house.

24:26.298 --> 24:28.500
You have to stop this.
You're hurting people.

24:28.567 --> 24:30.278
There is no conspiracy.
- I have been raided

24:30.302 --> 24:31.382
by the FBI.
- This is a lie.

24:31.436 --> 24:32.480
Tanya lied
about the whole thing.

24:32.504 --> 24:33.772
They are trying to silence me.

24:33.839 --> 24:34.949
- She made it all up.
- Kim, they are trying

24:34.973 --> 24:36.250
to stop you.
- Tell us where you are,

24:36.274 --> 24:37.418
and we will help you.
- Just keep looking

24:37.442 --> 24:39.010
for the truth.
- Tell us where you are.

24:41.079 --> 24:43.615
<i>I'm getting Mya back.</i>

24:43.682 --> 24:46.451
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:46.518 --> 24:48.353
We lost her.

24:48.420 --> 24:49.688
And we're out.
[bell rings]

24:49.754 --> 24:52.023
Get that thing out of my face.

24:52.090 --> 24:54.159
Did you get her?
- No, she hung up too soon.

24:54.226 --> 24:55.360
- Sheryll.
- Penny Fleming...

24:55.427 --> 24:58.163
I'm almost there.
Okay, 114 Serena Way.

24:58.230 --> 24:59.497
She's in Wilmington.
- Alert PD,

24:59.564 --> 25:01.032
get Kristin and Ray
over there now.

25:01.099 --> 25:03.335
We'll wait here
in case Kim calls back.

25:03.401 --> 25:10.342
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:14.813 --> 25:16.314
Officer Stone, Wilmington PD.

25:16.381 --> 25:17.983
- Did you clear the house?
- Yeah.

25:18.049 --> 25:19.117
She's the only one here.

25:19.184 --> 25:20.485
EMTs are on the way.

25:20.552 --> 25:21.553
Thank you.

25:23.321 --> 25:24.689
Hi, Penny.

25:24.756 --> 25:26.191
I'm Special Agent Ray Cannon.

25:26.258 --> 25:28.326
This is Special Agent
Kristin Gaines.

25:28.393 --> 25:29.227
Hi.

25:29.294 --> 25:31.329
So Kim did this to you?

25:31.396 --> 25:33.798
Yeah, she was on her phone,

25:33.865 --> 25:36.568
the FaceTime thing, and...
And as soon as she saw the FBI,

25:36.635 --> 25:37.869
she freaked out.

25:37.936 --> 25:40.272
She hung up
and started hitting me,

25:40.338 --> 25:42.007
asking me
where her daughter was.

25:42.073 --> 25:44.009
I told her I didn't know,
and then she left.

25:44.075 --> 25:45.353
Did she say where she was going?

25:45.377 --> 25:48.446
No, but she took
my laptop and my car.

25:48.513 --> 25:50.015
Why your laptop?

25:50.081 --> 25:51.283
She found something on it,

25:51.349 --> 25:53.752
but she wouldn't say
what it was.

25:53.818 --> 25:55.387
I thought she was gonna kill me.

25:55.453 --> 25:56.655
It's okay.
You're safe now.

25:56.721 --> 26:00.392
Excuse me a second.
I'm gonna call Remy.

26:00.458 --> 26:04.963
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:05.030 --> 26:06.932
Kristin, tell me it's good news.

26:06.998 --> 26:09.200
Yeah, Penny's alive,
but Kim took her laptop.

26:09.267 --> 26:10.402
She doesn't know why.

26:10.468 --> 26:11.946
Whatever's on it
probably saved her life.

26:11.970 --> 26:13.972
She also took Penny's car.

26:14.039 --> 26:15.507
<i>Set a perimeter.
Put a BOLO out.</i>

26:15.573 --> 26:17.742
Barnes and I
are headed to Middletown.

26:17.809 --> 26:19.611
A family whose son died at camp

26:19.678 --> 26:22.580
says they have info on Kim.

26:22.647 --> 26:23.682
[knocking at door]

26:23.748 --> 26:30.655
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:32.857 --> 26:34.059
I saw the interview.

26:34.125 --> 26:35.760
You got the proof, for real?

26:35.827 --> 26:38.930
In here.
You were right.

26:38.997 --> 26:39.997
Come on.

26:40.031 --> 26:44.235
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:44.302 --> 26:46.972
This is the third time
we've moved in four months.

26:47.038 --> 26:48.239
They keep finding us.

26:48.306 --> 26:50.075
Tanya doxxed you on her show?

26:50.141 --> 26:52.310
No, her followers do it
on their own.

26:52.377 --> 26:54.579
We get threatening letters,
calls all night long.

26:54.646 --> 26:56.614
These people come,
and they stand in the street,

26:56.681 --> 26:58.683
and they yell at our house.

26:58.750 --> 27:01.353
This one guy even followed me
around the grocery store,

27:01.419 --> 27:03.221
wanted to know
how much they paid us

27:03.288 --> 27:05.357
and where we were hiding Mason.

27:05.423 --> 27:07.492
- Did you tell the police?
- Many times.

27:07.559 --> 27:09.361
But it's not illegal
to dox someone,

27:09.427 --> 27:12.530
and it got worse
after we filed the lawsuit.

27:12.597 --> 27:14.265
What lawsuit?

27:14.332 --> 27:16.401
We're suing Tanya Waters
for defamation...

27:16.468 --> 27:18.236
All the families
whose kids have died,

27:18.303 --> 27:19.771
except for Kim Fogelman.

27:19.838 --> 27:20.998
When we asked her to join us,

27:21.039 --> 27:23.108
she told us Tanya
was exposing the truth...

27:23.174 --> 27:26.778
Accused us of being
part of some conspiracy.

27:26.845 --> 27:28.646
The very next day,

27:28.713 --> 27:31.182
this, uh, guy showed up,

27:31.249 --> 27:33.318
started trying to film us.

27:33.385 --> 27:35.320
<i>You should be
ashamed of yourselves!</i>

27:35.387 --> 27:37.422
<i>How much did they pay you, huh?</i>

27:37.489 --> 27:38.923
<i>Cops are on their way, buddy.</i>

27:38.990 --> 27:40.425
<i>Get off my property.</i>

27:40.492 --> 27:42.560
- Pennsylvania plates.
<i>- We know about the lawsuit!</i>

27:42.627 --> 27:45.964
<i>The whole world is gonna know
you're in on this cover-up!</i>

27:46.031 --> 27:47.632
<i>Sheryll, what's up?</i>

27:47.699 --> 27:49.901
We need you to run
some Pennsylvania plates.

27:49.968 --> 27:51.069
We might've found

27:51.136 --> 27:53.571
Kim Fogelman's
possible boyfriend.

27:53.638 --> 27:55.140
<i>[tense music]</i>

27:55.206 --> 27:57.208
Wolfgang Blair, FBI.

27:58.576 --> 28:00.145
Kim Fogelman, are you in there?

28:03.348 --> 28:05.150
Let's go.
- Breacher up!

28:07.118 --> 28:08.686
Go! Go, go!

28:08.753 --> 28:10.789
Check your six!

28:10.855 --> 28:12.123
Back room clear.

28:13.658 --> 28:15.026
Right clear!

28:15.994 --> 28:17.128
Back door, clear.

28:18.163 --> 28:19.264
Kitchen, clear.

28:21.699 --> 28:25.770
This has gotta be Penny's,
which means Kim was here.

28:25.837 --> 28:27.205
They wrecked it.

28:27.272 --> 28:28.773
Look at that.

28:28.840 --> 28:30.675
Had the whole conspiracy
laid out here.

28:30.742 --> 28:32.977
They're trying
to cover their tracks.

28:33.044 --> 28:37.148
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:37.215 --> 28:38.550
That's him.

28:42.320 --> 28:43.988
And look who he's with.

28:44.055 --> 28:45.657
Tanya Waters.

28:48.793 --> 28:51.896
"To a wonderful son.
Love, Mom."

28:51.963 --> 28:53.665
Wolfgang's Tanya's son.

29:01.206 --> 29:02.450
Aiding and abetting is a felony.

29:02.474 --> 29:04.042
He's looking at three years,
maybe more.

29:04.109 --> 29:05.286
You don't know he helped her.

29:05.310 --> 29:07.178
She could've taken him
at gunpoint.

29:07.245 --> 29:09.581
You seem really
concerned about that.

29:09.647 --> 29:11.116
I've been calling him
all morning.

29:11.182 --> 29:12.250
He won't pick up.

29:12.317 --> 29:13.418
How does he know Kim?

29:13.485 --> 29:14.752
Are they dating?

29:14.819 --> 29:16.121
I have no idea.

29:16.187 --> 29:18.223
I don't keep tabs
on Wolfie's love life.

29:18.289 --> 29:19.700
You see him every day.
He works here.

29:19.724 --> 29:21.826
Not true.

29:21.893 --> 29:23.795
He... he wants to be a reporter,

29:23.862 --> 29:25.396
but I made him start
at the bottom,

29:25.463 --> 29:28.433
so he manages
the message boards from home.

29:28.500 --> 29:30.135
Oh, yeah, what's his handle?

29:30.201 --> 29:31.769
@Wolfspider?

29:31.836 --> 29:33.238
Yeah,
he's all over these boards.

29:33.304 --> 29:35.607
Look at this.

29:35.673 --> 29:36.774
Mommy A?

29:36.841 --> 29:38.309
Or Mom Mya.

29:38.376 --> 29:40.345
Wolfgang first interacted
with her two months ago,

29:40.411 --> 29:42.156
and there's a bunch
of interactions ever since.

29:42.180 --> 29:43.891
That's how it started...
He connected with Kim

29:43.915 --> 29:46.684
on the boards, validated
her denial about the shooting,

29:46.751 --> 29:48.887
and filled her head
with conspiracy theories.

29:48.953 --> 29:50.498
He was pushing her
so he could be there

29:50.522 --> 29:51.789
to film it for TanyaDossier.

29:51.856 --> 29:53.591
He's trying
to get your attention.

29:53.658 --> 29:56.361
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:56.427 --> 29:58.730
You really don't get it,
do you, Tanya?

29:58.796 --> 30:00.532
They're working together.

30:00.598 --> 30:03.034
Well, I don't know what
I'm supposed to do about it.

30:03.101 --> 30:04.169
Go live.

30:04.235 --> 30:05.803
Say you made the whole thing up.

30:05.870 --> 30:07.438
Tell them to turn themselves in

30:07.505 --> 30:09.841
before this gets
a whole lot worse for Wolfgang.

30:09.908 --> 30:12.110
That would be career suicide.

30:12.177 --> 30:14.112
It's called telling the truth.

30:14.179 --> 30:16.314
You wouldn't do that
to save your own son?

30:16.381 --> 30:21.019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:21.085 --> 30:23.655
I'm gonna take a pass
on your invitation.

30:23.721 --> 30:27.492
Now, you have a job to do
and so do I.

30:27.559 --> 30:30.962
Why don't we all
get back to work?

30:31.029 --> 30:34.332
We're still on schedule.
Sound check, please.

30:34.399 --> 30:36.301
This is
Penny Fleming's bank statement

30:36.367 --> 30:38.403
from October 2022.

30:38.469 --> 30:41.339
That is a $100,000 deposit

30:41.406 --> 30:43.775
into her account
from the Wilmington Foundation,

30:43.841 --> 30:46.311
the charity owned
by Damon Marshall,

30:46.377 --> 30:48.179
leftist billionaire.

30:48.246 --> 30:50.782
He's the one orchestrating this
whole thing for the government.

30:50.848 --> 30:52.283
He paid Penny off

30:52.350 --> 30:54.652
so they could use her son
for the shooting,

30:54.719 --> 30:58.756
and he took the real kids,
including my daughter, Mya,

30:58.823 --> 31:01.960
and turned them
into crisis actors.

31:02.026 --> 31:04.896
These are the plans
to Marshall's home.

31:04.963 --> 31:07.899
I found them
on his architect's website.

31:07.966 --> 31:11.302
He has a secret bunker
in his house,

31:11.369 --> 31:13.204
right there.

31:13.271 --> 31:15.306
That's where
he's keeping the kids.

31:15.373 --> 31:17.175
That's where my Mya is,

31:17.242 --> 31:19.110
and I'm going to get her back.

31:19.177 --> 31:21.813
I'm gonna finally
expose the truth

31:21.879 --> 31:24.449
and bring my daughter home.

31:26.684 --> 31:29.287
Good, looking good.
Five minutes to air, people!

31:29.354 --> 31:31.756
Tanya, this is yours.
- Okay, thank you.

31:31.823 --> 31:34.926
[phone buzzing]

31:36.561 --> 31:37.862
Wolfgang's calling.

31:42.433 --> 31:43.433
Answer it.

31:45.470 --> 31:46.871
Tell the truth.

31:46.938 --> 31:48.406
This is your last chance, Tanya.

31:48.473 --> 31:51.576
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:51.643 --> 31:53.077
[phone beeps]

31:53.144 --> 31:54.144
Hello.

31:54.178 --> 31:56.314
Mom, it's me. You alone?

31:58.616 --> 31:59.884
Yeah.

31:59.951 --> 32:01.886
<i>Listen,
this is gonna be so epic,</i>

32:01.953 --> 32:03.153
<i>it's gonna break the internet.</i>

32:03.187 --> 32:05.823
We found Mr. X.
<i>- No, you didn't.</i>

32:05.890 --> 32:07.292
Yes, yeah, yeah, we did.

32:07.358 --> 32:10.261
He's a leftist billionaire,
and he runs a charity...

32:10.328 --> 32:12.130
Wolfgang, stop.

32:12.196 --> 32:14.899
Are you with Kim right now?

32:16.301 --> 32:17.635
Why?

32:17.702 --> 32:20.071
<i>Because I want you both
to hear this.</i>

32:23.875 --> 32:25.510
There is no Mr. X.

32:25.576 --> 32:26.944
[chuckles] What do you mean?

32:27.011 --> 32:28.889
You said that...
- I... I made him up, Wolfgang...

32:28.913 --> 32:30.848
Just like everything else.

32:32.250 --> 32:33.418
I was...

32:33.484 --> 32:35.520
I was trying
to tell a good story,

32:35.586 --> 32:39.190
<i>that those kids didn't die
in the camp shooting.</i>

32:39.257 --> 32:41.092
<i>I... I don't know,
I was just trying</i>

32:41.159 --> 32:44.762
to keep hope alive
'cause it was so awful,

32:44.829 --> 32:46.130
and you know, Wolfie,

32:46.197 --> 32:48.499
telling that story helped me

32:48.566 --> 32:51.936
<i>make a good life for you,
which...</i>

32:53.404 --> 32:55.907
As your mom,
is all I ever wanted to do.

32:57.642 --> 32:59.677
But that is all it was...

32:59.744 --> 33:01.646
A story.

33:01.713 --> 33:03.881
<i>Those kids are dead.</i>

33:03.948 --> 33:06.551
<i>Mya's dead.</i>

33:06.617 --> 33:08.753
<i>That is the true story.</i>

33:08.820 --> 33:12.757
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:12.824 --> 33:14.959
Now, I... I want you to come home.

33:15.026 --> 33:17.228
Stop all this nonsense with Kim.

33:17.295 --> 33:19.197
<i>No more people getting hurt.</i>

33:19.263 --> 33:20.998
You hear me, Wolfgang?
- Wha?

33:24.302 --> 33:25.603
Wolfgang?

33:27.004 --> 33:29.474
Do you hear me?

33:29.540 --> 33:31.843
Okay, I lost the location
ping, but the last known

33:31.909 --> 33:33.444
was Cape May, New Jersey,
headed north.

33:33.511 --> 33:35.847
Okay, billionaires
in Cape May...

33:38.549 --> 33:40.651
Are we live?

33:40.718 --> 33:41.919
Oh, yeah.

33:41.986 --> 33:43.354
Turn it off.

33:45.590 --> 33:47.058
You are so done.

33:47.125 --> 33:49.026
Yeah, and so are you.

33:50.661 --> 33:52.430
We're sick of all of this.

33:52.497 --> 33:53.831
Tanya, how could you?

33:53.898 --> 33:55.233
I trusted you.

33:56.901 --> 33:58.703
You're a heartless bitch.

33:58.770 --> 34:01.773
[indistinct chatter]

34:01.839 --> 34:03.074
I don't know.

34:03.141 --> 34:04.442
Cut the feed.

34:04.509 --> 34:06.277
Okay, Malik Pitney
has a place there.

34:06.344 --> 34:08.279
Elodie Dawes, Damon Marshall,

34:08.346 --> 34:10.014
Damon Marshall's
the angel investor

34:10.081 --> 34:11.882
behind
the Wilmington Foundation.

34:11.949 --> 34:13.226
He sent checks
to each of the families

34:13.251 --> 34:14.886
who lost kids
in the camp shooting.

34:16.954 --> 34:18.922
Get everyone
to the Marshalls' estate.

34:18.989 --> 34:21.192
Nice work, kid.

34:21.259 --> 34:23.327
Now, that's some damn good TV.

34:23.393 --> 34:30.333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:33.137 --> 34:35.505
As long as Lindsay approves.

34:35.572 --> 34:39.710
Yeah, we can take the money
out of, uh, out of operation...

34:39.777 --> 34:41.212
Hang... hang on a second.

34:43.080 --> 34:44.482
What in the world?

34:46.551 --> 34:48.686
Let... let me... let me...
Let me call you back.

34:48.753 --> 34:50.288
Damon Marshall!

34:50.353 --> 34:52.489
I know you're in there!

34:52.556 --> 34:53.824
Open the door,

34:53.891 --> 34:58.029
or I will shoot this man,
I swear!

35:00.097 --> 35:01.432
In.
- David, I'm sorry.

35:01.499 --> 35:03.067
She took...
- No talking!

35:03.134 --> 35:04.602
Take me to my daughter.

35:04.669 --> 35:05.937
What?

35:06.003 --> 35:08.172
I know she's here
with the other kids

35:08.239 --> 35:10.641
downstairs in the bunker.

35:10.708 --> 35:13.611
I promise you,
there is nobody here but me.

35:13.678 --> 35:15.155
[whispers]
Kim, maybe we should wait.

35:15.179 --> 35:16.414
We're not waiting.

35:16.481 --> 35:20.485
I wanna see my daughter...
And I wanna see her now.

35:27.625 --> 35:30.428
<i>[tense music]</i>

35:30.495 --> 35:34.298
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:34.365 --> 35:36.200
FBI is arriving on scene.

35:36.267 --> 35:38.135
<i>Right up ahead.
Approaching the estate.</i>

35:38.202 --> 35:39.770
Copy.

35:39.837 --> 35:40.738
- They inside?
- Yeah.

35:40.805 --> 35:42.907
Backup is two minutes out.

35:42.974 --> 35:44.509
Gaines and Gibson, around back.

35:44.575 --> 35:46.277
Sheryll and Ray, with me.

35:46.344 --> 35:52.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:52.149 --> 35:54.185
Kim Fogelman! FBI!

35:54.252 --> 35:56.621
Mr. Marshall!

35:56.687 --> 35:58.656
You in here?

36:01.359 --> 36:03.561
Don't you lie to me.

36:03.628 --> 36:06.564
Where is Mya?

36:06.631 --> 36:07.965
I know they're here.

36:08.032 --> 36:09.800
What did you do with them?
- Nothing.

36:09.867 --> 36:12.770
There has to be another room.

36:12.837 --> 36:15.740
No, do not waste my time.
- I'm not lying to you.

36:15.806 --> 36:18.409
I'm not wasting your time.
There's nobody here.

36:18.476 --> 36:20.011
I know they're here.

36:20.077 --> 36:21.922
What did you do with them?
- There's nobody here.

36:21.946 --> 36:23.848
- Tell me where they are.
- Please, please.

36:23.915 --> 36:24.815
I don't know
what you're talking about.

36:24.882 --> 36:26.050
There has to be here.

36:26.117 --> 36:27.461
Please, can you
just move the gun away?

36:27.485 --> 36:28.819
Tell me what you did with them.

36:28.886 --> 36:30.555
- I didn't do anything...
- Where is Mya?

36:30.621 --> 36:32.557
- There is no Mya here.
- Where is Mya?

36:32.623 --> 36:34.023
Do not tell me
that there is no Mya.

36:34.058 --> 36:36.227
Downstairs, hostage coming up.

36:36.294 --> 36:37.428
<i>Copy.</i>

36:37.495 --> 36:39.764
Please, I'm...
I'm trying to tell you...

36:39.830 --> 36:41.866
I don't have time for this.
You know who you...

36:41.933 --> 36:43.167
- [grunts]
- Put the gun away.

36:43.234 --> 36:44.745
- Hey, stop!
- FBI... drop your weapon!

36:44.769 --> 36:47.104
Put the gun down now!

36:47.171 --> 36:48.205
Come on, Kim!

36:48.272 --> 36:49.407
Let him go!

36:49.473 --> 36:51.542
- He has my daughter!
- No, he doesn't.

36:51.609 --> 36:53.311
Damon has nothing
to do with this.

36:53.377 --> 36:54.812
He paid off Penny Fleming.

36:54.879 --> 36:56.681
I saw the deposit.

36:56.747 --> 36:59.417
Do not step any closer.

36:59.483 --> 37:01.385
What, you mean the donation?

37:01.452 --> 37:03.221
Tell her, Damon.

37:03.287 --> 37:05.456
Wh...
What happened in the camp,

37:05.523 --> 37:06.857
it... it broke my heart.

37:06.924 --> 37:08.559
I mean, I... I... I felt awful,

37:08.626 --> 37:10.895
because Penny was a victim too.

37:10.962 --> 37:13.030
She lost her husband
and she lost her son,

37:13.097 --> 37:15.633
and I was
just trying to help her.

37:17.635 --> 37:19.670
I was being compassionate.

37:19.737 --> 37:21.706
He's just making that up!

37:21.772 --> 37:23.107
No, he's not, Kim.

37:23.174 --> 37:25.209
The only person making
things up is Tanya Waters.

37:25.276 --> 37:27.778
She admitted it on her show
this morning.

37:27.845 --> 37:31.649
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:31.716 --> 37:33.718
That's not true.

37:33.784 --> 37:35.786
She knows what really happened.

37:35.853 --> 37:38.756
Kim, I want you to listen to me.

37:42.460 --> 37:44.161
I'm a mother, too,

37:44.228 --> 37:47.164
and I know what it feels like
to go through a mass shooting.

37:47.231 --> 37:48.799
I was at the Brooklyn Point Mall

37:48.866 --> 37:50.146
with my family when it happened.

37:50.201 --> 37:51.936
Of course,
FBI agents were there.

37:52.003 --> 37:53.771
That was a fake too!

37:53.838 --> 37:55.349
No, it wasn't, Kim.
I saw the carnage

37:55.373 --> 37:56.974
with my own eyes.

37:57.041 --> 37:58.976
Now, I know you wanna believe
Mya's alive still.

37:59.043 --> 38:02.446
So do I, but she's not.

38:02.513 --> 38:03.981
She's not.

38:05.449 --> 38:07.418
You gotta stop
doing this to yourself.

38:07.485 --> 38:11.389
If you keep going, all you'll
find is your own pain, okay?

38:14.659 --> 38:16.861
Now put the gun down.

38:18.529 --> 38:19.563
Come on, Kim.

38:19.630 --> 38:23.334
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:23.401 --> 38:25.169
Put the gun down.
Damon, step to the side.

38:29.240 --> 38:31.509
[crying] Why?

38:31.575 --> 38:32.977
Why, why,
why'd it have to be Mya?

38:33.044 --> 38:35.212
Give me your hands.

